# Shell scripts and Dockerfiles MUST keep LF in the working tree, even on Windows.
# With core.autocrlf=true and no rule, a fresh Windows clone checks these out as
# CRLF. A CRLF shell script COPYed into a Linux Docker image breaks its shebang:
# the kernel tries to exec `/bin/sh\r` and fails with
# `exec docker-entrypoint.sh: No such file or directory` (exit 127, crash-loop).
# Scoped to these globs only, so other files keep their platform-native endings.
*.sh         text eol=lf
*.bash       text eol=lf
Dockerfile   text eol=lf
*.dockerfile text eol=lf
# Seeded verbatim as the container's crontab (Linux) — must stay LF.
crontab.default text eol=lf
